{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so the summary can attribute statements to attendees.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This can fail only when two model-dependent steps are exercised together: real diarized transcription output and downstream LLM attribution behavior. Mocks can hide label-format drift, missing diarization, or attribution loss across the handoff.","test_description":"Run the real pipeline on a multi-speaker recording with known speaker turns. Verify transcript chunks include stable speaker labels, then verify final structured summary attributes at least N sampled statements to the correct attendees. Repeat across a small set of recordings to catch model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.35,"Workflow":0.45}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Structured summary contains at least one action item for every attendee assigned a task.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on semantic extraction/assignment quality of the LLM. A mocked or deterministic parser would miss real omission errors where assigned tasks are not surfaced for specific attendees.","test_description":"Feed real transcripts (or gold transcript text) with explicit per-attendee assignments into the real summarization model. Assert each attendee with an assigned task appears in action items at least once. Run multiple trials/prompts to detect nondeterministic misses.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.15}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions in transcript appear in the structured \"decisions\" section, not only narrative text.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a model judgment/format-placement requirement. Mocked LLM outputs or rule-based fixtures can always place decisions correctly and miss real-world extraction/section-placement failures.","test_description":"Use real summarization calls on transcripts containing clearly phrased decision statements. Validate each gold decision is present in the `decisions` field and not only in freeform narrative sections. Execute repeated runs to detect placement instability.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.18}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"For audio longer than 60 minutes, service segments audio, processes sequentially, and merges into one coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Failure boundary spans orchestration plus multiple model-dependent steps over segments (transcribe/summarize/merge). Integration tests with mocks can miss real long-audio segmentation effects and cross-segment coherence loss.","test_description":"Run with a real >60-minute meeting recording. Assert segment boundaries are created, processed in order, and combined output is a single structured summary containing entities/threads from early and late segments without duplication or contradiction beyond threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.7}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"End-to-end pipeline (upload audio -> transcribe -> summarize -> deliver structured output) completes automatically for a real recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is explicitly a full pipeline requirement with real external AI services and sequential agentic stages. Lower levels cannot expose cross-step operational failures, retries/timeouts, or final delivery gaps.","test_description":"Execute a production-like end-to-end run using a real meeting file and real service endpoints. Verify no manual steps, terminal success status, and delivered structured payload with required sections (`action_items`, `decisions`, attendee attributions) within SLA.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.9}}]}
